Source/version control allows you to:
  -revert back to old coade
  -recover code
  -make multiple versions
  -compare two versions of code
  -prove a change helped
  -looked  back at change history
  -change another's code
  -share your own code
  -track when work is being done and by who
  -experiment without harming working code
  
Version control is a system that records changes to a file or set of files 
over time so you can recall specific versions later

VCS- version control system

local vcs- all versions stored in a directory
centralized vcs- central database has all versions; is accessible by multiple users for collaboration purposes
